nodes.title: Sam Settings
widgets_values:
This is the face detection... SAM

I use vit_b model for best results, and bboxface_yolov8n_v2 for detection, you can change that here if you want.

Detection settings are tuned quite well, but still mess up. I can't offer any advice here, as this is the best settings I have found to work.

Feel free to mess about here if you want.

Here you load in the completed video frames for upscaling one by one.

Upscaling can be anything, 1-3... i recommend 1.5-2

Current frame is the frame you are bringing in.  You can test it by doing a few images before you set the batches in the comfy ui menu, just set the increment to fixed to repeat the same frame.

When ready be sure to set the current frame to 0 and control after to increment, then in the comfy ui menu check extra options and set the batch number to your total frames.

If you cancel you can start again from the last frame you did by setting the current frame to the frame you want to start from.

Vivid sharpen can be bypassed if you dont want it.

nodes.title: Model Load Notes
widgets_values:
2 Model options, can use one for body and one for face if you want, just change the pipe used for each.

LCM lora is used here to speed up the process. I don't recommend using other loras, but I did not really test it

Clips skip should be set to your models' preference.

1 VAE only as I saw no need for 2, only 1.5 models can be used here due to using controlnets tile/pix2pix.

Fixed seed is best.

Saving the frames to a folder for further processing.

Choose the folder name to save the files in, default is 
myvideos\upscaled\yourfoldername

Next is off to the frame interpolation workflow.

nodes.title: Controlnet Upscale
widgets_values: Controlnet options here are tile and pix to pix.  Experiment, i prefer only tile here.  2 pipes to chose, just drag the pipe from the model you want to use to the sampler.  Default 1
Ip adaptor here helps with colouring and holding the pose.

Main Prompts

Enforce colors the video has, dont try to change too much.

nodes.title: Face Detailer notes
widgets_values:
CAUTION! - 

If any frames do not have a detected face, it will error.  If any frames in your video have no face showing, its best to disable the face detailer group.


This cuts faces out for enhancement after upscaling them, then pastes them back.  

This tries to fix the face as the final fix.  It works most of the time.

Prompt should be basic, but include eye colour for consistency.

Steps are 0-4 to 2-6. LCM sgm_uniform

Upscale to 512 768 1024

nodes.title: Body Enhancements notes
widgets_values:
This step cuts out people and enhances them before pasting them back to the image.  Uses the same prompt as the upscale

This step uses 2 control nets tile, and pix2pix.  Just tile works, but colours get changed to more dull.  

Prompt should not try to change clothing, the default works well for most.  You don't describe the background, only the person is paste back.

Can choose the model used by dragging the pipe from pipe 1 or 2 

Steps here can be 0-4 to 0-12.  Upscale from 1.25 to 2

2 pipes to choose from drag the pipe to the sampler for your chosen model

nodes.title: Welcome
widgets_values:
Welcome to the video subject upscale.  - All of this was copied and modified by me from my own image enhancing workflow.

This workflow can take a long while to complete with large upscales. This made/makes it hard to test properly with my 3060.

Upscaling videos is often difficult, this workflow aims to simplify and automate the process of cutting out subjects and faces of videos to enhance.

This workflow uses a batch system that uses Comfy UI's own batching system.  Located in extra options in the comfy UI menu. Batch count needs to be set to the number of frames you wish to process.  The frames are loaded one by one for processing to negate the large memory needed to do this step all at once.  It also allows the separation of people, and faces properly. 

This workflow uses controlnet pix2pix or tile and ip-adaptor plus to upscale without losing the fluidity of the movement.  

Pix2pix controlnet is highly recommended.
